messages.textToSpeech: This is the section of python interview

items.title: Q. What is Python?
items.description: A. Python is a high-level, interpreted, interactive and object-oriented scripting language. Python is designed to be highly readable. It uses English keywords frequently where as other languages use punctuation, and it has fewer syntactical constructions than other languages.

items.title: Q. Name some of the features of Python.
items.description:
A. It supports functional and structured programming methods as well as OOP.

It supports automatic garbage collection.

items.title: Q. Is python a case sensitive language?
items.description: A. Yes! Python is a case sensitive programming language.

items.title: Q. What are tuples in Python?
items.description: A. A tuple is another sequence data type that is similar to the list. A tuple consists of a number of values separated by commas. Unlike lists, however, tuples are enclosed within parentheses.

items.title: Q. What are Python's dictionaries?
items.description: A. Python's dictionaries are kind of hash table type. They work like associative arrays or hashes found in Perl and consist of key-value pairs. A dictionary key can be almost any Python type, but are usually numbers or strings. Values, on the other hand, can be any arbitrary Python object.

items.title: Q. What is the purpose of ** operator?
items.description: A. ** Exponent − Performs exponential (power) calculation on operators. a**b = 10 to the power 20 if a = 10 and b = 20.

items.title: Q. What is the purpose of // operator?
items.description: A. // Floor Division − The division of operands where the result is the quotient in which the digits after the decimal point are removed.

items.title: What is the purpose of is operator?
items.description: A. is − Evaluates to true if the variables on either side of the operator point to the same object and false otherwise. x is y, here is results in 1 if id(x) equals id(y).

items.title: Q. What is the purpose of not in operator?
items.description: A. not in − Evaluates to true if it does not finds a variable in the specified sequence and false otherwise. x not in y, here not in results in a 1 if x is not a member of sequence y.

items.title: Q. What is the purpose break statement in python?
items.description: A. break statement − Terminates the loop statement and transfers execution to the statement immediately following the loop.

items.title: Q. What is the purpose continue statement in python?
items.description: A. continue statement − Causes the loop to skip the remainder of its body and immediately retest its condition prior to reiterating.

items.title: Q. What is the purpose pass statement in python?
items.description: A. pass statement − The pass statement in Python is used when a statement is required syntactically but you do not want any command or code to execute.

items.title: Q. How can you pick a random item from a range?
items.description: A. randrange ([start,] stop [,step]) − returns a randomly selected element from range(start, stop, step).

items.title: Q.How can you get a random number in python?
items.description: A.random() − returns a random float r, such that 0 is less than or equal to r and r is less than 1.
